The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 ICC official to meet organisers 

 Champions Trophy

 Mumbai: The ICC is sending 

 its commercial manager Jamieson Campbell on Friday to meet 

 with representatives of the four staging centres of the 

 Champions Trophy in India.

 Jamieson Campbell will meet 

 the representatives of all the four Champions Trophy staging 

 centres on March 31 in Mumbai. The meeting is being held 

 to address some small issues before the ICC gives its final 

 clearance, informed a BCCI source on Wednesday.

 It has already been decided that 

 Mumbais Cricket Club of India, Jaipur, Mohali and 

 Ahmedabad are to host matches in the tournament with the 

 final to be held at the CCI.

 The BCCI working committee will 

 meet in Mumbai on April 9 to discuss the organisation of 

 Champions Trophy. 

 (PTI)




